<p><span class="lead-big">Statement Issued 26 October 2023</span></p>
<p>Dear staff and students</p>
<p>With the horrific conflict in the Middle East showing no sign of abating, I am writing to update you on support resources for students and staff affected.</p>
<p>Our thoughts are with all those affected by the conflict, both directly and indirectly. As a community of staff and students drawn from regions across the world, we will have family, friends and colleagues in the region and beyond who may really need our support and compassion right now.</p>
<p>I would encourage anyone affected in any way to call on the University’s support services, details of which are set out at the foot of this message.</p>
<p>At this time, it is more important than ever that we continue to express our views with respect and understanding, in line with our values as an inclusive, supportive community. There is no place at QMU for antisemitism, islamophobia, racism, religious or other intolerance or harassment. While we are unaware of any such incidents, if you experience or witness any such behaviour, you can report it directly through Report and Support, or seek support from the services listed below.</p>
<p>Please do not hesitate to get in touch if you feel you need to discuss anything with me on this subject.<br /><br /></p>
<p>Paul</p>
<p><br />Sir Paul Grice, FRSE, FAcSS<br />Principal and Vice-Chancellor<br /><br /></p>
